Kat answers some of my questions about prenatal and postnatal vitamins, the importance of sourcing quality, science backed ingredients, and gives great advice for fellow female entrepreneurs!

If you want to try @ritual for you or your family, use code ‘BABYLANE’ for 10% off your first 3 months 🤍

node.text:
5 Minute Makeup! 
Haven’t been getting glammed up lately for obvious reasons but wanted to share my go-to makeup for a quick, easy, effortless look. 🤍 also I did this on my phone and I have no idea what I’m doing but enjoy !!! Sunscreen / primer - @tula 
Concealer - @narsissist in vanilla 
Blush - @narsissist in Orgasm
Bronzer - @benefitcosmetics hoola 
Setting powder - @thekatvond in light 
Mascara - @lorealparis Lash Paradise 
Highlighter - @fentybeauty fire crystal 
Lip balm - @summerfridays

node.text:
Chris let me cut his hair... how do y’all think I did?! Fade could use some work but gotta start somewhere 😁 Thankfully @OldSpice partnered with us so we could show y’all how to become an at-home barber. If I can do it you can too! We want to see your before and after pictures so tag me, Chris and @OldSpice if you too have transitioned into the temporary barber role to help you or your significant other become their #BestSmellf. 
#SponsoredObviously

node.title: Cutting Chris’s Hair with Old Spice

node.text: Who else has been guilty of falling asleep without taking off their makeup or not cleansing immediately after a workout 💀 #ad You guys have heard me talk about my skincare regimen and the importance of cleansing so in celebration of Cleanse Your Skin Week, I wanted to show you how to get unready with me using my go-to @CeraVe cleanser and makeup removing cloths! Their unique formula with ceramides cleanses and removes dirt/oil so gently — it’s a must for my sensitive skin. #CleanseYourSkinWeek #CeraVe

node.text: @zerofusshaircare has been my life/time/styling saver (especially with how consuming motherhood is!). The products smell so good and make my natural curls look so healthy without hot tools! I'm challenging myself with their ‘No Blow Dry July’ air-drying challenge, and would love for you guys to join me. @zerofusshaircare is giving away free product, check out their page for more information! #ad

node.text: 5 weeks in and we could all use a vacation 😅 starting to get some smiles which makes even the sleepiest days and nights SO worth it. We barelyyyy squeeze into our 0-3 month clothes and weigh just about 11 pounds. But also I’ve never worried so much in my entire life and I don’t think I’ll ever stop worrying even when he’s 40and oh my gosh when he starts driving I think I’ll sleep even less ahhhh ndndisnasuchsjw!!. Lastly- super bummed this fit didn’t have a matching bucket hat :/

node.text: Part of me didn’t want to share this photo because it really isn’t a realistic representation of what breastfeeding has been like for me. It’s been hard and honestly painful at times and quite the opposite of glamorous. With the help of a lactation consultant we’ve somewhat corrected this little snapping turtles latch and are making so much progress but I still worry  if he’s getting enough, if my body is doing it’s job, and often wonder ‘why isn’t today going as well as yesterday, is it my fault?’ I didn’t know Chris was taking this photo and although it’s not necessarily representative of our reality for the first two weeks, I want to frame it and keep it forever. because even through the pain and frustration I can’t help but smile watching you. I have cherished this special time with you sweet Dutton and I am incredibly thankful for a healthy, growing baby 💙 any moms please comment pumping / breastfeeding tips pls and thank u!
